lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4829  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6: Immunolabeling of protein 4.1B (EPB41L3) with the synaptic markers PSD95 (DLG4, marker for PSD) and synapsin 1 (SYN1, marker for presynapse) at 4, 8 and 12 DIV. Co-localization with the postsynaptic marker was consistently higher than its presynaptic counterpart.\n\nA more specific subcellular localization cannot be annotated from the presented data although the functional assays imply localization at or near the postsynaptic specialization/PSD together, co-localizing with receptors.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Medium density hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 19 Sprague Dawley rat pups as described (Brewer et al., 1993), with minimal modifications\"\n\nuniprot accession for rat species selected for this annotation was closest to the reviewed mouse uniprot accession Q9WV92.\n\nantibody / targeting:\n\"To generate shRNA to mouse 4.1B, the following sequence of 4.1B was subcloned into the pSuper vector (Brummelkamp et al., 2002): 5'- CGTGACCGGCTTCGAATAA -3.\"\n\nNucleotide BLAST top-hits are all from gene EPB41L3, e.g. NM_001395724." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4829" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

